const title = "Perlick Commercial Refrigeration Repair LA — Same Day";
const description = "Perlick commercial reach-in + bar back cooler repair across LA, OC, Ventura. Signature Series HC/HP, Sottile, ADA, pass-through. EPA 608, $120 commercial dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's covered on this page versus your other Perlick pages?",
    a: "This page is for commercial refrigeration — Signature Series HC and HP reach-ins, Sottile narrow undercounter, ADA-compliant commercial models, pass-through bar units, bar back coolers used purely for cold storage, and commercial prep tables. If your Perlick is a draft beer system or kegerator with tap towers, beer-line cooling, or CO₂ regulation, the right page is /brands/perlick-draft-beer-system-repair/ — that's where our beer-side specialists work and where the tap-system parts inventory lives. If your unit is a residential or outdoor undercounter for home use, see /brands/perlick-refrigerator-repair/ or /brands/perlick-outdoor-refrigerator-repair/. We treat these as separate practices because the parts and the diagnostic order differ."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Perlick still independent or has it been acquired?",
    a: "Perlick is a Wisconsin family company in business since 1917, independently owned and operated as of this writing. It has not consolidated into the Ali Group, Welbilt, Standex, or other major foodservice equipment conglomerates that have absorbed many heritage brands over the last two decades. We confirm current ownership status against the manufacturer's own corporate page when ownership questions matter for warranty or parts-source decisions; if you need a current verification before you make a purchase decision, the Perlick corporate site is the authoritative reference."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you carry Perlick OEM parts on the truck?",
    a: "Common wear parts for Signature Series HC and HP reach-ins ride on every commercial truck: door gaskets in the standard hinge configurations, evaporator and condenser fan motors, defrost timers and heaters, common door switches and hinges, drain heaters. Sottile-specific parts (narrow 18\" chassis) and ADA-compliant model parts ship from Perlick distribution, typically 1-3 business days. Pass-through unit parts depend on configuration — we order through Perlick authorized distribution for those. We do not substitute aftermarket compressors or control boards on Perlick — the brand's stainless-steel commercial construction is part of what justifies the service-life premium, and pairing that chassis with bargain-basement compressors throws away the longevity advantage."
  },
  {
    q: "Same-day commercial dispatch for Perlick downtime?",
    a: "Yes. Bar refrigeration downtime is unforgiving — a back-bar cooler that fails at 4 PM with a Friday-night service starting at 6 PM costs a venue more than the repair will. We dispatch commercial calls priority, and most Perlick service requests received before 2 PM get a tech on-site the same business day. Phones answered 24/7, scheduling triage moves commercial refrigeration ahead of residential whenever a venue is down. For multi-unit hospitality groups, we can set up direct-dispatch protocols and named account management."
  },
  {
    q: "How long should a Perlick Signature Series reach-in last?",
    a: "Perlick's commercial line is built closer to specification refrigeration than typical mid-tier foodservice — heavier-gauge stainless, higher-grade door gaskets, premium compressor sourcing. Service life on Signature HC and HP reach-ins commonly runs 14-18 years with routine maintenance, sometimes longer if the operating environment is mild and the condenser cleaning is on schedule. Sottile and ADA-compliant models share the same construction quality. The single biggest variable is the LA microclimate and venue type — a hot bar back room with airborne grease will shorten service life faster than a temperature-controlled cellar. Quarterly condenser cleaning makes the difference between 12 years and 18."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you handle bar and restaurant service contracts?",
    a: "Yes. Multi-unit accounts (hotel bars, restaurant groups, hospitality companies with several venues) get a named account manager and net-30 invoicing after the first visit. Quarterly preventative maintenance contracts cover condenser cleaning, gasket inspection, drain-line flush, refrigerant-charge verification under EPA 608, and door-cycle testing. We document each visit for HACCP and health-department records. For venues with mixed Perlick equipment (commercial reach-ins on this page, plus draft beer systems on /brands/perlick-draft-beer-system-repair/), we coordinate visits so a single dispatch covers both refrigeration practices."
  }
];

